    A static utility class that provides operations related to 'Type' model objects.

    The following operations are supported:

    • Create Association
    • Get Associations
    • Conforms To

        public static org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Association createAssociationFromProperty(org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Property property,
                                                                             boolean end1IsNavigable,
                                                                             org.eclipse.uml2.uml.AggregationKind end1Aggregation,
                                                                             boolean end2IsNavigable,

                                                                             String end2Name,
                                                                             int end2Lower,
                                                                             int end2Upper)
        Creates a(n) (binary) association between this type and the specified other type, with the specified navigabilities, aggregations, names, lower bounds, and upper bounds, and owned by this type's nearest package.
        Parameters:
        type - The receiving 'Type' model object.
        end1IsNavigable - The navigability for the first end of the new association.
        end1Aggregation - The aggregation for the first end of the new association.
        end1Name - The name for the first end of the new association.
        end1Lower - The lower bound for the first end of the new association.
        end1Upper - The upper bound for the first end of the new association.
        end1Type - The type for the first end of the new association.
        end2IsNavigable - The navigability for the second end of the new association.
        end2Aggregation - The aggregation for the second end of the new association.
        end2Name - The name for the second end of the new association.
        end2Lower - The lower bound for the second end of the new association.
        end2Upper - The upper bound for the second end of the new association.
